115
00:05:42,776 --> 00:05:44,344
Well, that's wrong always.

116
00:05:44,378 --> 00:05:47,448
Here's my thing... creativity
is not a flavor, Tony.

117
00:05:49,683 --> 00:05:53,020
Most hawker stalls
are family-run operations.

118
00:05:53,053 --> 00:05:55,322
And Whampoa is no exception.

119
00:05:55,355 --> 00:05:57,725
What's unusual is that
Li Ruifang

120
00:05:57,758 --> 00:06:01,161
left her white-collar job
to work alongside her parents,

121
00:06:01,194 --> 00:06:03,931
bucking a trend that has
left the hawker centers

122
00:06:03,964 --> 00:06:05,566
with an aging workforce,

123
00:06:05,599 --> 00:06:08,669
unable to replenish
generations of expertise

124
00:06:08,702 --> 00:06:12,406
with new blood.

125
00:06:12,440 --> 00:06:14,300
If you look around, Tony,
you look at all the hawkers,

126
00:06:14,307 --> 00:06:18,746
more than 70%, 80% of them
are 50 and above.

127
00:06:18,779 --> 00:06:21,415
So the tipping point will come
where everybody just give up.

128
00:06:21,449 --> 00:06:22,643
They're stalled, because their
children have gone

129
00:06:22,650 --> 00:06:24,251
to university.

130
00:06:24,284 --> 00:06:26,887
They have told them, yeah, go...
Go be a doctor, lawyer.

131
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:30,190
Go be something else
other than a hawker.

132
00:06:30,223 --> 00:06:32,793
But the Singaporean government
wants to build more stalls...

133
00:06:32,826 --> 00:06:34,962
More, better, modern.

134
00:06:34,995 --> 00:06:36,089
20 more hawker centers,
actually.

135
00:06:36,096 --> 00:06:37,731
20 more hawker centers.

136
00:06:37,765 --> 00:06:39,560
Which I say, where the hell
are the hawkers coming from?

137
00:06:39,567 --> 00:06:41,635
- Well, that's a good question.
- Yeah, yeah.

138
00:06:41,669 --> 00:06:43,437
Where are they gonna come from?

139
00:06:43,471 --> 00:06:45,599
There's a lot of insinuations
of an answer but no true answer.

140
00:06:45,606 --> 00:06:47,708
I mean, the answer's
not from Singapore, right?

141
00:06:47,741 --> 00:06:49,543
They're gonna have to come in
from China.

142
00:06:49,577 --> 00:06:53,781
For the 15,000 or 20,000
food stalls

143
00:06:53,814 --> 00:06:55,215
I guess we have in Singapore,

144
00:06:55,248 --> 00:06:57,250
if it's public-run like this,

145
00:06:57,284 --> 00:06:58,819
you can't hire foreigners.

146
00:06:58,852 --> 00:07:00,488
It's meant for Singaporeans.

147
00:07:00,521 --> 00:07:02,756
But isn't the beginning
of all of this...

148
00:07:02,790 --> 00:07:06,059
Was people from China, India...?

149
00:07:06,093 --> 00:07:08,496
That's why I keep saying

150
00:07:08,529 --> 00:07:09,897
our food came from...

151
00:07:09,930 --> 00:07:10,957
- Somewhere.
- The rest of the world.

152
00:07:10,964 --> 00:07:12,666
Yeah, we had nothing.

153
00:07:12,700 --> 00:07:14,768
And in that tradition, I say,

154
00:07:14,802 --> 00:07:16,970
