00:35:07,539 --> 00:35:09,975
That's hard.

769
00:35:10,008 --> 00:35:12,110
Sauce goes good with the rice.

770
00:35:12,144 --> 00:35:13,645
Thank you, mmm.

771
00:35:13,679 --> 00:35:14,646
It's fantastic.

772
00:35:14,680 --> 00:35:16,682
Wow, that's good.

773
00:35:19,718 --> 00:35:23,455
♪

774
00:35:23,489 --> 00:35:26,192
Choi has been making this dish
for decades:

775
00:35:26,225 --> 00:35:28,794
pigs' feet cooked slowly
in black vinegar,

776
00:35:28,827 --> 00:35:30,529
ginger, fried chilies,

777
00:35:30,562 --> 00:35:31,763
and asam.

778
00:35:31,797 --> 00:35:32,297
♪

779
00:35:35,967 --> 00:35:38,304
Chap chye is
a Hainanese family favorite:

780
00:35:38,337 --> 00:35:41,673
cabbage and glass noodles
stir-fried with bean curd,

781
00:35:41,707 --> 00:35:43,542
black mushrooms, pig skin,

782
00:35:43,575 --> 00:35:44,776
and shrimp.

783
00:35:44,810 --> 00:35:45,310
♪

784
00:35:49,315 --> 00:35:51,217
Now, I've been speaking
to a lot of people

785
00:35:51,250 --> 00:35:54,853
who talk about how Singapore
loves its hawker culture.

786
00:35:54,886 --> 00:35:56,522
It loves its food.

787
00:35:56,555 --> 00:35:59,825
But the general story is,

788
00:35:59,858 --> 00:36:03,229
the first generation
starts a hawker stall.

789
00:36:03,262 --> 00:36:05,731
They get successful, they send
the kids to school,

790
00:36:05,764 --> 00:36:08,734
they tell them, "Do not...
I did not work hard"

791
00:36:08,767 --> 00:36:10,802
so you could go in
the restaurant business."

792
00:36:10,836 --> 00:36:12,904
My dad and mom
say the same thing.

793
00:36:12,938 --> 00:36:15,241
Don't come into the business.

794
00:36:15,274 --> 00:36:16,908
Get a nine-to-five job.

795
00:36:16,942 --> 00:36:19,578
Stay in an air-conditioned room.

796
00:36:21,112 --> 00:36:23,415
Many of the people
I speak to are very sad

797
00:36:23,449 --> 00:36:26,718
that these original recipes
and preparations

798
00:36:26,752 --> 00:36:28,387
are disappearing.

799
00:36:28,420 --> 00:36:29,914
You know, other than
this wonderful family,

800
00:36:29,921 --> 00:36:31,757
who... who do your parents think

801
00:36:31,790 --> 00:36:34,360
will keep these
traditions alive?

802
00:36:36,061 --> 00:36:38,430
My mom was saying, like,
now that the government

803
00:36:38,464 --> 00:36:41,600
encourage a lot of young people
to preserve our traditions

804
00:36:41,633 --> 00:36:43,001
and all, so I think it should...

805
00:36:43,034 --> 00:36:44,836
Even hope that ten years
down the road,

806
00:36:44,870 --> 00:36:47,673
maybe more people like us
or younger generation

807
00:36:47,706 --> 00:36:49,875
are going to take
over the business.

808
00:36:49,908 --> 00:36:53,379
And right now, Wayne's
eldest daughter is 14.

809
00:36:53,412 --> 00:36:55,714
Yeah, we are making sure she
help out in the shop

810
00:36:55,747 --> 00:36:57,849
on weekends, so to learn
and understand

811
00:36:57,883 --> 00:37:01,853
it's not easy to...
To earn, like...

812
00:37:01,887 --> 00:37:03,047
What, would you like
your child to stay

813
00:37:03,054 --> 00:37:04,623
in the restaurant business?

814
00:37:06,292 --> 00:37:09,428
Yeah, so if they're really
interested in this industry,

815
00:37:09,461 --> 00:37:10,696
why not?
I would just, yeah.

816
00:37:10,729 --> 00:37:12,130
- You'd say yeah.
- Yeah.

817
00:37:12,163 --> 00:37:13,799
- Yes.
- This is so good, by the way.

818
00:37:13,832 --> 00:37:15,301
This is delicious food.

819
00:37:15,334 --> 00:37:16,968
Mm-hmm.

820
00:37:21,006 --> 00:37:23,942
Now, Singapore
is a rich country.

821
00:37:23,975 --> 00:37:25,344
Lot of rich people live here.

822
00:37:27,245 --> 00:37:29,881
Why can't you charge
as much money

823
00:37:29,915 --> 00:37:31,817
for this traditional food

824
00:37:31,850 --> 00:37:33,552
as the French charge
for French food?

825
00:37:33,585 --> 00:37:36,154
What do you think?
Why won't Singaporeans pay?

826
00:37:36,187 --> 00:37:39,257
Actually, just a couple
of months ago,

827
00:37:39,291 --> 00:37:41,126
we go through some of our
old photos,

828
00:37:41,159 --> 00:37:44,496
and there's one photo that is
like almost 20 years ago

829
00:37:44,530 --> 00:37:46,264
that's priceless.

830
00:37:46,298 --> 00:37:48,834
They're selling their fried rice
at $3, okay?

831
00:37:48,867 --> 00:37:50,802
Right now, we are selling $4.

832
00:37:50,836 --> 00:37:52,771
So...
20 years later.

833
00:37:52,804 --> 00:37:55,140
One dollar more.

834
00:37:55,173 --> 00:37:56,775
Why?

835
00:37:56,808 --> 00:37:58,644
Singaporeans love food.

836
00:37:58,677 --> 00:38:01,513
I think there's like a bond
between us and the customers.

837
00:38:01,547 --> 00:38:03,782
So he doesn't want
to increase the price.

838
00:38:03,815 --> 00:38:05,150
- You know your customers.
- Yeah.

839
00:38:05,183 --> 00:38:06,618
Right, you have
a lot of regulars.

840
00:38:06,652 --> 00:38:08,119
Yeah. A lot of them is like,

841
00:38:08,153 --> 00:38:09,855
they seen us growing up,
the three of us.

842
00:38:09,888 --> 00:38:11,690
And we see their kids
growing up.

843
00:38:11,723 --> 00:38:14,693
So I think that's a different
kind of bond between us

844
00:38:14,726 --> 00:38:15,994
and the customers.

845
00:38:16,027 --> 00:38:17,596
I just hope this
doesn't disappear,

846
00:38:17,629 --> 00:38:20,932
because it's of course always
gonna be the good stuff.

847
00:38:20,966 --> 00:38:23,535
It's important.
Can I have a little more?

848
00:38:23,569 --> 00:38:25,537
Can we get a little more?

849
00:38:25,571 --> 00:38:26,905
Delicious food.

850
00:38:58,404 --> 00:39:01,172
Singapore is a multinational
society.

851
00:39:01,206 --> 00:39:04,175
We got Chinese, Malay, Indian,
other Asians in Singapore.

852
00:39:04,209 --> 00:39:07,446
- It seems to work.
- It works, it works, yes!

853
00:39:15,921 --> 00:39:16,421
♪

854
00:39:31,437 --> 00:39:33,705
One last trip straight back

855
00:39:33,739 --> 00:39:35,441
to where it all started for me.

856
00:39:35,474 --> 00:39:35,974
♪

857
00:39:40,579 --> 00:39:42,380
A simple, good thing.

858
00:39:42,414 --> 00:39:44,950
In this case, one of my
favorite things.

859
00:39:44,983 --> 00:39:45,483
♪

860
00:39:52,624 --> 00:39:55,126
Ah, here it is, the mighty
char kway teow.

861
00:39:55,160 --> 00:39:57,028
Ordinarily, this is a breakfast.

862
00:39:57,062 --> 00:39:58,797
I eat it every time
I'm in Singapore.

863
00:39:58,830 --> 00:40:01,366
It's just about the unhealthiest
breakfast you could have.

864
00:40:01,399 --> 00:40:06,638
I mean, it's literally,
like, lard...

865
00:40:06,672 --> 00:40:08,907
crispy lard bits.

866
00:40:08,940 --> 00:40:11,610
Healthy cockles.

867
00:40:11,643 --> 00:40:15,146
Shrimp paste, and a whole
lot of noodles.

868
00:40:15,180 --> 00:40:17,148
And it's, like,
legendarily fattening.

869
00:40:17,182 --> 00:40:21,653
Originally created for...
To feed laborers.

870
00:40:21,687 --> 00:40:23,789
So...

871
00:40:23,822 --> 00:40:25,591
it isn't pretty.

872
00:40:25,624 --> 00:40:28,594
Not the healthiest of breakfast.
Delicious.

873
00:40:29,961 --> 00:40:31,797
Mmm.

874
00:40:31,830 --> 00:40:35,934
You're looking to fit into
that silver lamé Speedo,

875
00:40:35,967 --> 00:40:37,836
this would not be, uh...

876
00:40:37,869 --> 00:40:39,605
option one.

877
00:40:39,638 --> 00:40:41,740
Oh, man.

878
00:40:41,773 --> 00:40:43,341
Problem is, you eat this

879
00:40:43,374 --> 00:40:45,911
surrounded by all these
sort of wonders of Asia

880
00:40:45,944 --> 00:40:48,179
in the food court here,

881
00:40:48,213 --> 00:40:50,782
and after this,
you're kinda done.

882
00:40:50,816 --> 00:40:53,184
I don't know how anybody
works after this, frankly.

883
00:40:56,888 --> 00:40:58,049
Once in a while, you hit
a little piece

884
00:40:58,056 --> 00:40:59,525
